This paper deals with the problem of predicting user affinity to items, which is a common problem in machine learning and recommender systems. The paper specifically focuses on the use of bilinear random effect models (matrix factorization) for binary response data, which is a popular technique in the field of machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category for this paper is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), as these sub-categories are closely related to the topic of recommender systems. Additionally, the paper also discusses parallel computing techniques, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
